-- Steel Dynamics Forecasts Profit That Trails Estimates on Recycled Metals
-- Christopher Donville
-- 2010-06-16T21:57:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/steel-dynamics-forecasts-profit-that-lags-analysts-estimates-shares-fall.html

          
          
             Steel Dynamics Inc. , the fourth-
largest U.S.-based steelmaker,  forecast  second-quarter earnings
that trailed analystsâ€™ estimates amid decreased profit margins
on recycled metals and lower sales of flat-rolled steel.  
 Earnings-per share will be 20 cents to 25 cents, Fort
Wayne, Indiana-based Steel Dynamics said today in a statement.
Analysts projected profit of 34 cents, the average of 12
 estimates  in a Bloomberg survey.  
 The company reported per-share  earnings  of 29 cents a share
in the first quarter and a net loss of 8 cents in the second
quarter of 2009.  
 Steel Dynamics fell 24 cents, or 1.7 percent, to $13.97 at
5:23 p.m. after the close of regular Nasdaq Stock Market
trading.  The shares  had declined 20 percent this year at the end
of the trading day.  
 Nucor Corp. , U.S. Steel Corp. and AK Steel Holding Corp.
are the three largest U.S. steelmakers by 2009 revenue.  
